      "Deployment follows need: the assessment names the risk or goal (falls at night, seizure detection, wandering with road danger, medication prompts, loneliness and contact), considers the human alternatives honestly, selects the least intrusive technology that meets the need, and writes the deployment into the care plan with its response arrangements — technology fitted because it came with the flat, or because the catalogue was persuasive, fails the gate",
