    purpose: "This policy prepares the service for the day its systems turn hostile or dark — the ransomware note where the care records were, the compromised email quietly forwarding referrals, the payroll diverted by a convincing invoice. Care services are soft targets holding hard-to-replace data, and the difference between a bad week and an existential event is decided before the incident: by backups that restore, paper that is ready, and people who know their first hour.",
    scope: "Covers cyber incident preparedness and response: prevention basics, detection and the first-hour drill, care continuity on manual fallbacks, the notification map, recovery and the ransom question, and post-incident learning. It extends the business continuity policy (wl-007/gov-007) into the cyber domain and runs igr-003's breach machinery where personal data is involved.",
